    MapData
    AC.earth - XEarth for Java
    MapDataReader
    The map data file is a big array of short (16-bit) ints, as follows: - it is a sequence of closed curves - the first value in a curve is the number of points in the curve - the second value in a curve indicates land/water (1 or -1, respectively) - this is followed by an [x,y,z] triple that indicates a point on the unit sphere (each of x, y, and z has been scaled by 30000), where the x axis points "to the right" (towards 0 N 90 E), the y axis points "up" (towards the north pole), and the z axis points "out of the screen" (towards 0 N 0 E).
